  "text": "With some slight creative adjustments, specialised equipment to tear cotton strips used in soil decomposition assays (e.g. Mecmesin Ultra Test Tensiometer, Mecmesin, UK) can also be applied to directly measure leaf tensile strength (J. H. C. Cornelissen, unpubl. data) . Good, alternative leaf-shearing methods are also available (e.g. [CITATION_1] . In all such cases, interspecific comparisons are possible, but for broad comparisons combining different methods, we strongly recommend calibration against one of the above devices as well as including cotton strips (see above).",
